# Admin UI (jsonConfig)

## Files

- `admin/jsonConfig.json` — UI definition (source of truth for labels/help)
- `admin/i18n/*.json` — 11 languages (de, en, es, fr, it, nl, pl, pt, ru, uk, zh-cn)

## jsonConfig guidelines

- End-user friendly labels; tooltips for complex options
- Sensible defaults; validation on required fields
- New options need a default in `io-package.json` → `native`

## Translations

After changing labels/help in jsonConfig:

1. Run `npm run translate`
2. Ensure no orphaned or missing keys in i18n files
3. Keys sorted alphabetically; native language text (no English fallbacks in non-en files)

## Config ↔ adapter

Every jsonConfig field must exist in `io-package.json` → `native` with a default value.
